01:00:38.400 --> 01:00:44.440
And just pull your… yes, just, you see?

01:00:44.440 --> 01:00:45.170
See, this one is.

01:00:45.170 --> 01:00:55.320
Perspiring, this hand.
It’s perspiring too, it’s interesting.

01:00:55.320 --> 01:00:57.821
You have been to no guru or anyone like that?

01:00:57.821 --> 01:00:58.863
(Man: “No”) To no-one?

01:00:58.863 --> 01:01:03.343
(Man: “Yes”) Have you been reading&nbsp;
these third-eye people and all that?

01:01:03.343 --> 01:01:05.520
(Man replies no) Something about, what you call…
Yogi: He says he has a problem&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:01:05.520 --> 01:01:12.910
with his mother.
Shri Mataji: Good.

01:01:12.910 --> 01:01:13.520
(A yogini tells Shri Mataji about some connection&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:01:13.520 --> 01:01:24.000
of the seeker’s mother with&nbsp;
the Hare Krishna) Krishna?

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:24.600
Hare Rama.

01:01:26.080 --> 01:01:28.137
Only his mother has been.

01:01:28.137 --> 01:01:39.320
(Yogini: “Yes…”) He has not been to anything.

01:01:39.320 --> 01:01:43.122
You feel alright otherwise, normally?

01:01:43.122 --> 01:01:43.148
(Man: “Yes”) Alright.

01:01:43.148 --> 01:01:45.880
(Other man: “Sometimes he can&nbsp;
get a pain (?) in the temple&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:01:45.880 --> 01:01:49.200
here build up”)
Build like that.

01:01:49.200 --> 01:01:50.840
And then, what about your sleeping?

01:01:50.840 --> 01:01:55.177
You feel nice, you get nice&nbsp;
sleep or you feel restless?

01:01:55.177 --> 01:02:00.720
(Man: “Just think”)
Just think so?

01:02:00.720 --> 01:02:01.720
Now good.

01:02:01.720 --> 01:02:02.747
See, see how cold his feet are.
Yogi: Void.&nbsp;

01:02:02.747 --> 01:02:07.147
Shri Mataji: Eh?
Yogi: Void.&nbsp;

01:02:07.147 --> 01:02:09.240
Shri Mataji: But he says&nbsp;
he’s not been to any guru.

01:02:09.240 --> 01:02:11.870
What sort of books you read, what are you doing?&nbsp;

01:02:11.870 --> 01:02:13.894
Man: What am I doing?
Shri Mataji: Ha.

01:02:13.894 --> 01:02:22.520
(Man: “I’m just living in a place just waiting to&nbsp;
live in the country…”) What are you doing there?

01:02:22.520 --> 01:02:24.800
In the flat, in the country?

01:02:30.600 --> 01:02:31.540
What do you do?

01:02:31.540 --> 01:02:37.800
(Unclear reply – he said he took&nbsp;
drugs but he has given up.) Alright.

01:02:38.400 --> 01:02:50.160
But little drugs you take sometimes.
That’s why Void, that’s why the Void.&nbsp;

01:02:50.160 --> 01:02:55.600
No, no, it’s not the mother’s point, you see,&nbsp;
it’s the Void, his, his own problem is the Void.

01:02:55.600 --> 01:03:00.920
Do you get nervous here in the stomach sometimes?

01:03:00.920 --> 01:03:06.160
Sometimes you do, isn’t it?

01:03:06.160 --> 01:03:17.200
Is Void.
He is better?

01:03:17.200 --> 01:03:25.760
The hands are not perspiring so much, are they?

01:03:26.840 --> 01:03:49.989
Know you can give up drugs,&nbsp;
no difficulty, you see?

01:03:49.989 --> 01:03:50.061
Just you decide you’ll give up, hm?
(Man: “Yes”) It’s better now?

01:03:50.061 --> 01:03:50.600
Good.
You see, with some people&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:03:50.600 --> 01:03:55.040
I’ve seen, drugs don’t have so much&nbsp;
effect, but some are very sensitive.

01:03:55.040 --> 01:03:56.711
It won’t suit you.

01:03:56.711 --> 01:03:58.200
See, you are a saint.

01:03:58.200 --> 01:04:01.180
You can’t take drugs.

01:04:01.180 --> 01:04:21.160
You see – how white the whole thing has become.
Better now.

01:04:21.160 --> 01:04:21.535
Now, come up?

01:04:21.535 --> 01:04:23.520
(Yogi: “It’s started to cool”) Good.

01:04:23.520 --> 01:04:25.280
He’s a saint, you see.

01:04:25.280 --> 01:04:34.040
That’s why he, even little drugs&nbsp;
is, is, I can’t even… it depends on,&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:04:34.040 --> 01:04:37.000
see, what fiber you are made of.

01:04:37.000 --> 01:04:39.920
Some people I’ve seen they’ll&nbsp;
take drums full of it,&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:04:39.920 --> 01:04:44.360
nothing happens, you see, they&nbsp;
don’t get into drugged condition.

01:04:44.360 --> 01:04:55.080
Some people get it so much, and&nbsp;
it affects some people very much.&nbsp;

01:04:59.040 --> 01:05:00.143
Better now.
Better now?

01:05:00.143 --> 01:05:04.904
(Man: “Yes”) Are you feeling cool breeze?

01:05:04.904 --> 01:05:09.532
(Man: “No”) No, that’s it.

01:05:09.532 --> 01:05:10.660
Your Agnya is there, still.
You are from Birmingham?

01:05:10.660 --> 01:05:15.000
Man: No.
Shri Mataji: From where?&nbsp;

01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:17.000
Man: From London.
Shri Mataji: From London?&nbsp;

01:05:17.000 --> 01:05:25.640
Man: Yes.
Shri Mataji: Alright.

01:05:25.640 --> 01:05:31.480
They are perspiring.
Just put your hand there.

01:05:31.480 --> 01:05:32.600
Very slow heart.

01:05:32.600 --> 01:05:46.440
(Inaudible conversation with a&nbsp;
yogi) You must take to garlic.&nbsp;

01:05:46.440 --> 01:05:55.640
Now, in his case you have to raise the right.
Just the opposite of it.&nbsp;

01:06:08.960 --> 01:06:15.280
Better now?

01:06:15.280 --> 01:06:18.560
Now, is it better?
Man: Still heavy.&nbsp;

01:06:18.560 --> 01:06:20.467
Shri Mataji: Eh?&nbsp;

01:06:20.467 --> 01:06:21.240
Man: Still feels heavy in the right.
Shri Mataji: Ah, that’s it.

01:06:21.240 --> 01:06:24.440
To raise it.

01:06:24.440 --> 01:06:25.560
You’ll be alright.

01:06:37.400 --> 01:06:42.280
Just look at your father, he’s enjoying himself.

01:06:42.280 --> 01:07:13.291
He wrote a very nice letter to Me.
What do you say?&nbsp;

01:07:13.291 --> 01:07:13.319
Yogi: Agnya.
Shri Mataji: Eh?&nbsp;

01:07:13.319 --> 01:07:15.440
Yogi: Agnya is there (?).
Shri Mataji: Is better now, see?

01:07:15.440 --> 01:07:17.340
Is improving.
But right side very weak.

01:07:17.340 --> 01:07:25.520
You work out.&nbsp;

01:07:35.600 --> 01:07:42.600
Sort of receding, you recede, you know?
You recede away from things, isn’t it?&nbsp;

01:07:42.600 --> 01:07:48.400
I mean, you don’t like the world, sort&nbsp;
of thing, you want to recede away?

01:07:48.400 --> 01:07:51.160
That’s what happens to you, is it?

01:07:51.160 --> 01:07:55.440
Because people are nasty.

01:07:56.520 --> 01:08:00.360
(Man says something) Eh?

01:08:00.360 --> 01:08:13.200
But you just don’t… you… what do you feel&nbsp;
about life as such, what do you think?

01:08:13.200 --> 01:08:23.611
Like frustrated?
Man: Yes.

01:08:23.611 --> 01:08:25.200
I spend money…
Shri Mataji: That.&nbsp;

01:08:25.840 --> 01:08:26.680
Man: Yes.

01:08:26.680 --> 01:08:28.682
And worry about money…
Shri Mataji: Eh?&nbsp;

01:08:28.682 --> 01:08:29.440
Man: Worry about money…
Shri Mataji: It’s alright.&nbsp;

01:08:29.440 --> 01:08:41.600
Man: …feel a bit dejected (unclear).
Shri Mataji: You’re not to be dejected, alright?

01:08:41.600 --> 01:08:42.800
You need to come up.

01:08:42.800 --> 01:08:45.320
A little.

01:08:45.320 --> 01:08:50.461
Ha! See now.

01:08:50.461 --> 01:08:52.040
(Yogi: “Agnya”)
Better now?

01:08:52.040 --> 01:08:54.520
Feeling better?
Man: More&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:08:54.520 --> 01:08:56.360
fresh, alright.
Shri Mataji: More fresh.

01:08:56.360 --> 01:09:04.147
That’s it.
Man: This is tinglish… (?)&nbsp;

01:09:04.147 --> 01:09:05.480
Shri Mataji: You see, that’s it, you see?

01:09:05.480 --> 01:09:06.956
It’s a thing moves from one to that.

01:09:06.956 --> 01:09:06.960
Yes?

01:09:06.960 --> 01:09:11.080
(A small child speaks to Shri Mataji: … flower…)
That’s good.

01:09:11.080 --> 01:09:13.960
You think if I give him the&nbsp;
flower he’ll feel better?

01:09:13.960 --> 01:09:15.280
Alright.

01:09:15.280 --> 01:09:21.827
You see, her son is saying ‘alright,&nbsp;
just you have the flower, let’s see’.

01:09:21.827 --> 01:09:28.187
(She laughs) Now, is it better?
Man: Right starts to get heavy.

01:09:28.187 --> 01:09:30.627
Shri Mataji: Eh?
Man: Right starts to get heavy.

01:09:30.627 --> 01:09:31.400
Shri Mataji: Heavy.

01:09:31.400 --> 01:09:32.027
Right.
Man: Yes.&nbsp;

01:09:32.027 --> 01:09:39.840
Shri Mataji: Ah.

01:09:46.840 --> 01:09:52.807
It’s heavy.

01:09:52.807 --> 01:09:55.805
(After some silence during which&nbsp;
there is probably some workout) So.

01:09:55.805 --> 01:09:56.542
Man: It’s slightly…
Yogi: It’s still…&nbsp;

01:09:56.542 --> 01:09:59.040
Shri Mataji: Now you are better now.

01:09:59.040 --> 01:10:00.120
Are you?

01:10:00.120 --> 01:10:01.800
How are you feeling?

01:10:01.800 --> 01:10:04.340
Are you feeling any cool breeze?&nbsp;

01:10:04.340 --> 01:10:07.200
Man: Slightly.
Shri Mataji: Slight.

01:10:14.640 --> 01:10:16.960
What is there to be worried about money?

01:10:16.960 --> 01:10:18.800
[Man: “To be worried?

01:10:19.920 --> 01:10:25.440
I guess from that I invested&nbsp;
some money and I’m worried that&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:25.440 --> 01:10:33.635
… (indistinct words)… to do&nbsp;
these things”] To… to do?

01:10:33.635 --> 01:10:35.320
Man: To do all these things that&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:10:35.320 --> 01:10:40.480
I intend to do … (inaudible sentence)
Shri Mataji: Where have you invested?

01:10:40.480 --> 01:10:40.980
Eh?

01:11:11.680 --> 01:11:15.697
But you have invested money into what projects?

01:11:15.697 --> 01:11:15.928
(Inaudible sentence of the man.

01:11:15.928 --> 01:11:31.503
Then says some words sounding like “Selling&nbsp;
marijuana” Somebody explains: “Selling drugs.”)&nbsp;

01:11:31.503 --> 01:11:41.640
Shri Mataji: Oh! That’s&nbsp;
dangerous! They are cheats!&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:11:41.640 --> 01:11:42.720
They are cheats! (Man: “They won’t sell&nbsp;
drugs”) No, they can cheat you, they are.

01:11:42.720 --> 01:11:53.400
It’s obviously, this is such a bad traffic!

01:11:53.400 --> 01:11:57.195
Money is not everything.

01:11:57.195 --> 01:11:58.160
Yes, that’s it.

01:11:58.160 --> 01:12:04.480
And that’s why they can cheat you.
Alright?

01:12:04.480 --> 01:12:06.480
Now, I’ll give them a bandhan.

01:12:06.480 --> 01:12:09.840
But if you get your money back, then&nbsp;
you are not going to go into it anymore.

01:12:09.840 --> 01:12:10.800
Alright?

01:12:10.800 --> 01:12:26.160
That’s the promise.
Alright.

01:12:28.080 --> 01:12:31.360
You are literally, absolutely fagged out.

01:12:31.360 --> 01:12:32.920
You know?

01:12:32.920 --> 01:12:35.680
You may not.

01:12:35.680 --> 01:12:40.794
You have to look after yourself.
See, the Void is all moving.&nbsp;

01:12:40.794 --> 01:12:48.075
Yogi: Especially on the right side in here.
Shri Mataji: In here.

01:12:48.075 --> 01:12:54.760
Void is, the lower side.

01:12:54.760 --> 01:12:55.260
Now.

01:12:55.680 --> 01:13:02.880
I would suggest for him, tell him the Void mantra.

01:13:02.880 --> 01:13:05.000
Put him on the photograph.

01:13:05.000 --> 01:13:09.080
Let him work it out, it will clear.

01:13:09.080 --> 01:13:13.880
That will solve your financial problem also.
You see, it goes simultaneously.

01:13:13.880 --> 01:13:16.120
Alright?
It’s a problem of your Nabhi.

01:13:16.120 --> 01:13:20.020
He’ll give you the mantra and you work it out.

01:13:20.020 --> 01:13:24.745
For a week, then come and see Me.

01:13:24.745 --> 01:13:34.226
(To the yogis) And also of Nabhi.
(Yogi: “Yes”) Alright.

01:13:34.226 --> 01:13:34.231
Good.

01:13:34.231 --> 01:13:34.960
(A small child’s voice is heard)
Should be alright.

01:13:34.960 --> 01:13:35.640
Eh?
Small child: Should&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:13:35.640 --> 01:13:40.920
I work on somebody?
Shri Mataji: On whom do you want to work?

01:13:40.920 --> 01:13:43.840
Work on hand, let’s see.

01:13:43.840 --> 01:13:45.440
Eh?

01:13:45.440 --> 01:13:47.560
Work on Me.

01:13:47.560 --> 01:13:50.360
I see! (Shri Mataji laughs)&nbsp;
That’s the easiest to do, eh?

01:13:50.360 --> 01:13:55.720
Very nice… See!
I’ll work on you, that’s the&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:13:55.720 --> 01:14:01.400
best! (Shri Mataji kisses the child and laughs)
So, who wants to work on, the new baby: see?

01:14:01.400 --> 01:14:14.113
Wonderful! Nobody else, they don’t want&nbsp;
to work on anybody else: he’s very clever!

01:14:14.113 --> 01:14:14.440
Ah ah ah! Ah ah ah! Ah ah&nbsp;
ah! What is there to work?

01:14:14.440 --> 01:14:15.520
Just to take love!
